<subSubSection id="102B980E92C28C3E6BD9A03B92BAF52A" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="CD9D7DF4CDB1EB474CC7A2029892631F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6426DA1AA028318730C090404F1A1211" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
A rare, local and range-restricted Balkan endemic shared between North Macedonia and Greece. It has been recorded with certainty only from the Prilep area (North Macedonia) and Mt. Orvilos (NE Greece, see 
<bibRefCitation id="C91CA3B12C2B546A2E2E3588D09B197A" author="Gamal-Eldin, E." journalOrPublisher="Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668143" refString="Gamal-Eldin, E., Wagenitz, G., 1991. Mountain Flora of Greece 2. Edinburgh University Press, Edinburgh" title="Mountain Flora of Greece 2" year="1991">Gamal-Eldin and Wagenitz 1991</bibRefCitation>
). The new locality on Falakro (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0B653E72C81AA40600E1390CA5DC8627" captionStartId="F7677561" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">6</figureCitation>
) adds a new mountain locality to the 
<normalizedToken id="9C1151EF75A4EF4C47770D63DBE503F2" originalValue="species’">species'</normalizedToken>
distribution, which is thus extended to the east (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="50F561A47F0DFA628DF0B709506C2583" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7677570" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of Centaurea marmorea, Jacobaea othonnae subsp. anomala, Hesperis matronalis subsp. matronalis and Saponaria stranjensis in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656686" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
